@jayush have initiated the request as per your comments, could you please check and let me know why I am seeing this checks failure.

Was Ambari forcing it to lower case to enforce a convention/standard for queue naming?
We currently follow lower-case-only convention in all our YARN production and dev clusters.

HI @mithmatt  ,

Actually in WEB UI we were trying to create the ID for each of queue as path.toLowerCase() , so if mutliple queue path exists and its not case sensitive its causing this issue. 

you can refer to this code : https://github.com/Akhilsnaik/ambari/blob/origin/trunk/contrib/views/capacity-scheduler/src/main/resources/ui/app/serializers.js#L89 
in which we are creating the queue object later which will be added to ArrayObject which demands unique Id and due to which AMBARI-23122  happens,

Please fell free to review and approve my changes.
